Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.99,0:00:05.35,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}From a different point of view, even an imposing\Nwall blocking your path is just a large door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.35,0:00:07.06,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We finally figured out the upside-down trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.06,0:00:09.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An incomplete novel, and a cornered killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.70,0:00:11.16,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:12.79,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.79,0:00:14.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.17,0:01:47.38,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My name is Toshihisa Manda, and I'm a novelist who was locked in a hotel in order to finish a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.01,0:01:50.26,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I sneaked out of the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.26,0:01:54.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and murdered my disciple\Nand ghostwriter, Kohei Haramoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.85,0:01:58.27,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After that, I snuck back to the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.29,0:02:01.04,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}in order to forge an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.04,0:02:02.92,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}While we were playing baseball,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:06.71,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}we lost control of the ball, which went flying into Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.71,0:02:09.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, we went to his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.22,0:02:15.97,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...where we found him murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.23,0:02:25.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.86,0:02:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys came to get your ball,\Nand when you reached this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.20,0:02:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you found this man on the floor\Nwith blood around his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.20,0:02:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably murdered\Nduring an attempted theft.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.50,0:02:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the room doesn't look particularly messy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.37,0:02:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was somebody he knew!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.13,0:02:45.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.42,0:02:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.88,0:02:52.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a sign on the door outside saying Do not enter!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.05,0:02:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. So?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.47,0:02:56.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{If a robber saw the sign, they'd know to avoid this room because somebody was inside! – loose match}This means somebody's on the other side of the door writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.22,0:02:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! And if you open the door, you'll get spotted right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.43,0:03:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There'd be no way to get behind him without him noticing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.48,0:03:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{If I were an intruder and wanted to murder this man,}If it was me, I'd start making some noise on purpose, and once the victim came out of the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.48,0:03:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{I'd wait outside the door with a grin and ambush him.}I'd be waiting for him with the weapon ready to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.70,0:03:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're scary, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.24,0:03:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The point is, Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must've let the killer in himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.83,0:03:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was someone he knew... Like this man here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.33,0:03:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did the forensics say was the estimated time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.17,0:03:27.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roughly two hours ago, around 3pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.75,0:03:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.46,0:03:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was locked up in a room at the New Beika Hotel so I could finish my latest novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.64,0:03:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The New Beika Hotel isn't far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.47,0:03:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd only take a couple of minutes by car or less than ten minutes by bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.39,0:03:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, were you with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.52,0:03:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I was sitting in front of the lifts next to the room where {\i1}Sensei{\i0} was.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.03,0:03:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he'd have to pass through there to leave the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.07,0:03:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I don't think {\i1}Sensei's{\i0}\Nthat good at sneaking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.58,0:04:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did he finish the novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.95,0:04:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez! Don't tell me you suspect me of murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.96,0:04:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no! Just following procedure, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.92,0:04:08.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.50,0:04:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Well, he finished the novel around 4pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.59,0:04:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, I looked over it in his hotel room, and took a taxi with him to his home, to talk about his next novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.01,0:04:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.52,0:04:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{Do you know of anyone who might have had a grudge against Haramoto-san}Do you know if Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} might have any friends with grudges against him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.90,0:04:29.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beats me. He was a private person.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.69,0:04:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{We hardly ever talked about anything but work.}He told me he wanted to be a novelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.57,0:04:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{He organized my projects.}so I gave him jobs like revising my manuscripts and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.74,0:04:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you'll find many of my manuscripts on his computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.78,0:04:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,including ones I never finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.04,0:04:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{Did you hook him up with this house?}A while ago, you mentioned that you're the one who let him live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I used to live here with my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.00,0:04:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it got too small for us, so we built a new house across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.13,0:05:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, my sons have all grown up and my wife has passed on, so I live alone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.64,0:05:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to demolish this house, so I let him live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.23,0:05:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place is pretty clean for a bachelor pad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.77,0:05:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A housekeeper comes in once a week...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.15,0:05:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.32,0:05:21.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} likes to keep things tidy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.41,0:05:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, there's nothing in this drawer but a mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.99,0:05:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.87,0:05:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's blood and broken pieces of vase on the mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.71,0:05:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...but the middle of the drawer is clean!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.63,0:05:38.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Almost like there was something here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.18,0:05:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.72,0:05:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the murderer was after the contents of this drawer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.56,0:05:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea what it might be, Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.27,0:05:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er... No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.06,0:05:49.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:52.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, isn't it about time you noticed something {\i1}really{\i0} odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.02,0:05:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! There's something even stranger about this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.11,0:05:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stranger?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.28,0:06:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look around this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.70,0:06:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the shelves!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.99,0:06:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The miniature cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.99,0:06:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...the dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.99,0:06:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...the books...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.95,0:06:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're all upside-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.50,0:06:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kids are right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.50,0:06:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.58,0:06:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.25,0:06:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.05,0:06:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that your cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.01,0:06:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't let your cat run around a crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.30,0:06:24.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry... I was so focused on this that I forgot all about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.14,0:06:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Inspector! The back door!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.22,0:06:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.81,0:06:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a private residence!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.35,0:06:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ichimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.23,0:06:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... You're here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.32,0:06:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.74,0:06:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It wasn't me! I'm just the housekeeper!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.49,0:06:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.62,0:06:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, do you have any idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.83,0:06:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.96,0:06:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... It's probably one of Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s pranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pranks?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.46,0:06:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He was always pulling ridiculous pranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.55,0:07:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like piling his slippers in a tower...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.05,0:07:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...or loosening all the light bulbs in the house so they wouldn't turn on...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.51,0:07:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...or leaving video tapes in a row in the hall causing a domino effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.39,0:07:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he'd spy on my reaction with a creepy grin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.44,0:07:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he'd just look at me with an innocent face while I have to clean everything up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.44,0:07:24.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{You have no idea how many times I got mad at him!}That's why I'm sure this is just more of the same. Because he knew I'd be arriving at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.70,0:07:27.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, it's just a prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.99,0:07:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it makes sense it's a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.16,0:07:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Apparently he was pretty childish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.33,0:07:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, we thought it was some kind of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.79,0:07:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.38,0:07:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't turn them upside-down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.13,0:07:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer did!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:41.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.97,0:07:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at those books!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.76,0:07:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The covers are crumpled up, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.43,0:07:49.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever turned them over did it in a hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.14,0:07:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are toy cars with their side mirrors broken off
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.35,0:07:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and figurines that have fallen out of their boxes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:58.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was apparently a very important\Ncollection to Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.57,0:08:03.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he wanted to prank the housekeeper, I'm sure he'd be more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.24,0:08:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. The housekeeper arrived roughly two hours after the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.74,0:08:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knew when to expect her, so there wouldn't be any rush to set this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.99,0:08:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.37,0:08:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would the killer do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, it was to hide something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.21,0:08:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd stand out if {\i1}one{\i0} thing was turned upside-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.26,0:08:25.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...so the murderer turned {\i1}everything{\i0} over to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.13,0:08:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, may I leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.39,0:08:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time I got back to the editorial office.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.31,0:08:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can come back once you've finished proofreading, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.98,0:08:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still want to talk about my next book!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.19,0:08:42.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}, I really don't think it's appropriate to discuss a mystery novel on a day like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.82,0:08:44.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.70,0:08:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you wrote period novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.45,0:08:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At my age, it's time to try something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.66,0:08:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{In fact, I've already started working on it!}In fact, I don't have much left to do on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.25,0:08:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, even what's on the shelf seems rather well lined-up...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.04,0:08:58.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... More than half of them are mystery novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.42,0:09:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} loved detective novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.92,0:09:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always said his debut would be with one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.97,0:09:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had such an interesting idea for the detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.80,0:09:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Ichimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Did he ask you to bring anything today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.52,0:09:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.06,0:09:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used to send you out to shop for things for his collections.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.56,0:09:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially when he didn't have time to get out of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.53,0:09:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.86,0:09:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted me to call him in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.91,0:09:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right! He wanted me to set up a dental appointment for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.87,0:09:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.74,0:09:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just that when I called him from the hotel earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.58,0:09:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...he was telling me how excited he was to complete some set.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.04,0:09:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't worry. He was probably talking about one of his absurd collections.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.84,0:09:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You called him today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.09,0:09:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.22,0:09:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I often call him when I'm stuck in work... for a change of pace...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.51,0:09:54.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did he sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.77,0:09:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like his usual self.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.14,0:09:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.27,0:10:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.06,0:10:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you figured out who the killer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.15,0:10:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.32,0:10:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer didn't hide something by turning things upside-down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.90,0:10:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He {\i1}thought{\i0} he could hide it\Nby turning them upside-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.33,0:10:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer didn't hide something by turning stuff upside-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.04,0:10:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...but he {\i1}thought{\i0} he'd hide it by turning stuff upside-down?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be more exact, he {\i1}thought{\i0} it'd be hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.38,0:10:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hidden...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.00,0:10:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.80,0:10:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof, we have what the killer said to interrupt just before it could come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.01,0:10:34.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.51,0:10:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's{\i0} the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.14,0:10:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.89,0:10:42.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come back after proofing this manuscript at the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.56,0:10:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, may I go too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.60,0:10:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to start preparing for a meeting, and want to drop off my cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.44,0:10:49.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.65,0:10:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Feel free to call me if anything comes up, I live right across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.61,0:10:54.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's making a run for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.78,0:10:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should we let him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.49,0:11:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Your next book will be your first detective novel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.50,0:11:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.12,0:11:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to read it! I just love mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.67,0:11:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it's on Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s PC.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.72,0:11:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.80,0:11:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you cheering him on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.72,0:11:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you gonna corner him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.06,0:11:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing you, I'm sure you're up to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.64,0:11:29.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it time you wiped that smug grin off your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay! I'll tell you the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.15,0:11:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only if you agree to help!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.28,0:11:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.16,0:11:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.45,0:11:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{I can't believe he has the nerve to plan a meeting with his editor now.}His protegé's murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.95,0:11:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he has the nerve to set up a meeting to talk about a mystery novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.83,0:11:44.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.83,0:11:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.29,0:11:49.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.84,0:11:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This toy car is broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.30,0:11:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the side mirror has snapped off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.22,0:11:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.43,0:12:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the person who moved the items was in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.22,0:12:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.43,0:12:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did this to play a prank on the housekeeper, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.48,0:12:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Because he knew she'd be arriving at 5 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.99,0:12:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This collection probably wasn't all that important to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.91,0:12:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that novel writer told us...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.08,0:12:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...how excited Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was about getting a complete set!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.50,0:12:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question is, what collection did he complete?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.33,0:12:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but from those words alone, there's no way to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.79,0:12:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could be talking about cars or figurines or sets of books...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.71,0:12:36.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Complete set?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.43,0:12:38.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In a hurry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.14,0:12:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? You got a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.68,0:12:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah, it's the cat hair! It's all over this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.10,0:12:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cat hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.60,0:12:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nlet his cat run around this room
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.61,0:12:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,even while the police were searching the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.11,0:12:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No wonder there's so much cat hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.78,0:12:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.57,0:13:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.99,0:13:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came here because he heard something break,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.79,0:13:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then saw us entering here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.37,0:13:10.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he followed us in case we were dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.75,0:13:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd never bring my kitty into danger like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.55,0:13:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if I did, I'd keep him in his carrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.01,0:13:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could step on something sharp and hurt himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.18,0:13:21.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.64,0:13:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like he let his cat run around on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.85,0:13:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let his cat run around on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.89,0:13:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Detective Yako Hyakki allowed a smile to paint itself upon his harshly closed lips.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.07,0:13:43.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, accepting the investigator's word...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.04,0:13:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is as far as it goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.67,0:13:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You took longer than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.59,0:13:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, yes, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.76,0:13:58.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran into some trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.63,0:14:04.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, {\i1}Sensei{\i0}, why don't you tell me about this detective novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.14,0:14:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You say you've already started work on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.43,0:14:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. In fact, I'm almost to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.77,0:14:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just wondering how to wrap it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.02,0:14:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, in this murder case,\Nthe detective is the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.90,0:14:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.92,0:14:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, the story is about an attorney who's murdered at the beginning of the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.24,0:14:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She possesses the body of a friend of hers, a police detective, to solve her own murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.62,0:14:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah... That sounds interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.00,0:14:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our attorney/detective's\Nname is Yako Hyakki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.09,0:14:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has a ring to it, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.88,0:14:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could it be at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.76,0:14:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but could this wait until after my meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.60,0:14:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We think you can spare us the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.98,0:14:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, we've solved the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.69,0:14:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Solved the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.73,0:14:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:14:57.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.44,0:14:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who murdered Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.23,0:15:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...was {\i1}you{\i0}, Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.95,0:15:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.20,0:15:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the famous novelist, is a murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.29,0:15:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} locked in his hotel room working since the previous night,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.29,0:15:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and thus would still be there at 3pm,\Nthe time of the crime? {this could probably be divided}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.79,0:15:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The editor, Shimaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, probably wasn't watching the door the whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.67,0:15:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he probably snuck out in disguise as a bellhop or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.22,0:15:31.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he probably took a bicycle or something similar he'd prepared in advance to Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.56,0:15:35.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a careless moment, he beat him to death with a vase,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.81,0:15:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and rushed back to the hotel to create a perfect alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.36,0:15:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there was a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.15,0:15:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. The cat you had with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.24,0:15:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It ran away from the room where the crime took place to the adjacent room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.04,0:15:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You searched the house, but the cat was hiding somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.75,0:15:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when you remembered something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.08,0:15:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That before you killed Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.84,0:16:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he'd mentioned finally having a complete set of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.51,0:16:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You live across the street from Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.34,0:16:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that if you left the back door open, the cat would come back to your house when it got hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.22,0:16:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But before that, he'd walk all around the house, all over the collection that Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had just finished today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.15,0:16:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we found those cat hairs, we'd have proof you'd come to this house today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.40,0:16:25.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you and your cat
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.61,0:16:29.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were supposed to have been locked up working in that hotel room since the night before!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.20,0:16:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when you came up with an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.24,0:16:34.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you turned all of his collectibles upside-down,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.70,0:16:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then when the housekeeper came in two hours and set everything right,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.17,0:16:41.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she'd knock the cat hair off the items!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.21,0:16:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... But what if the cat hair stayed on anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.97,0:16:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't need to fall off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.97,0:16:51.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just needed Ichimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to tell the police she'd touched the items!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.85,0:16:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cat hair on the floor could've got stuck on the toy cars while she was flipping them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.23,0:17:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why bother to turn\Neverything upside-down?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.73,0:17:06.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not just knock things to the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that wouldn't look like a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.07,0:17:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she thought it was the work of a thief,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.03,0:17:14.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she might call the police without touching the crime scene, ruining the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.33,0:17:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we went into the room before the housekeeper got there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.71,0:17:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! That's why\NManda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was so nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.63,0:17:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he had to use his brain a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.46,0:17:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw us entering that house,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he hurried over with his cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.26,0:17:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and let it run around the house so it could get hair on everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.81,0:17:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why he got upset when we tried to pick the cat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.31,0:17:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we held the cat until the police came, his plan wouldn't have worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.82,0:17:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he still managed to cover up the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:17:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With no proof, he can say you're just making everything up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.62,0:17:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I left a perfect bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.58,0:18:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wonderful deduction, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.92,0:18:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I advise you to become a mystery novelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.30,0:18:14.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where's the proof? If you don't have any proof, you can't arrest me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.14,0:18:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I'm not the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.56,0:18:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think I'll use that deduction in my next novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.44,0:18:25.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of mystery novels, we found one on Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.73,0:18:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An unfinished manuscript\Nstarring a ghost detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.07,0:18:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...named Yako Hyakki!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.45,0:18:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.70,0:18:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked Shimaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your editor, to cooperate with us and wired his clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.13,0:18:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard you're working on a novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.92,0:18:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...about a ghost detective with the same name!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.09,0:18:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.93,0:18:48.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haramoto kept copies of all my rough drafts!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.89,0:18:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you wrote that manuscript?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.77,0:18:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.23,0:19:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be honest, the children were playing on the computer when they stumbled upon the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.15,0:19:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My men and I read it along with them, hoping it might contain some clue to Haramoto's murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.24,0:19:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I have to admit I wasn't sharp enough to guess the ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.74,0:19:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe you'd be kind enough to tell me who the murderer in the story is, and the trick that was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.91,0:19:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.46,0:19:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, you wouldn't let us see the CD case with the CD you stole from Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s drawer,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.88,0:19:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as that case should still have his blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.59,0:19:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were reading it just now, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.55,0:19:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As after returning from the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.56,0:19:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you found Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body and didn't come back home until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.81,0:19:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as you were with your editor since then, leaving you with no time to read it beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.48,0:19:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And despite that, you were telling Shimaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the entire story just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.65,0:19:48.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me that boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.53,0:19:51.20,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't wait to read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.20,0:19:53.79,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I wonder if it's on Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s PC.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.81,0:19:59.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did he push me to read the manuscript right away so I wouldn't have time to hide the disc?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.31,0:20:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That CD and its case...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.60,0:20:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're in your house, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.03,0:20:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.65,0:20:14.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm no {\i1}sensei{\i0} anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.24,0:20:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just an old man whose fire went out after his wife's passing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.33,0:20:24.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, my work over the last two to three years was written by Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.92,0:20:29.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first I heavily revised his drafts\Nbefore publishing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.80,0:20:33.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then he started complaining\Nabout my revisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.85,0:20:35.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{He wouldn't let me have any say in what he wrote for me.}And lately, I couldn't find anything\Nwrong with his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.97,0:20:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.77,0:20:42.52,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Please... Just stay in the bleachers and let me do my stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.52,0:20:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've already passed the torch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.03,0:20:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those words were so depressing and humiliating...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.82,0:20:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't forgive him for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.03,0:20:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did you steal his mystery novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.08,0:21:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was overcome with the idea that\NI could write it better than he could.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.92,0:21:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.42,0:21:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how much I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.88,0:21:09.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no idea who the killer was, or what trick he used.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.47,0:21:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I never was cut out to be a mystery writer...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.85,0:22:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was the housekeeper's comments who gave you the clue?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.48,0:22:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.48,0:22:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, when she was trying to tell us about the detective that Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came up with,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.23,0:22:54.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} interrupted her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.19,0:22:56.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when I realized he was trying\Nto steal Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s work!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.70,0:22:58.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That just leaves one mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.82,0:23:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the murderer in the novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.87,0:23:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! The complete set\NHaramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.58,0:23:06.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.75,0:23:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably talking about his teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.75,0:23:10.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.54,0:23:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The housekeeper, Ichimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, said she'd made a dental appointment for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.55,0:23:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was a mirror inside the drawer Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was looking into when Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.27,0:23:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, among the vase's fragments inside the drawer, there was a dental piece.{might need a proper EN term here}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.44,0:23:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell Inspector Megure about something this important?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.49,0:23:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he already knew who the killer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.57,0:23:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, forensics will tell him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:23:45.62,Signs,,0,0,0,,ha
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:23:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.59,0:23:54.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A death threat?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.55,0:24:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The writer was murdered\Nby a character from her novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.80,0:24:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer must be trying\Nto confuse the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.60,0:24:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But was that the only objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.19,0:24:17.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.22,0:24:22.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Sushi ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.27,0:24:23.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What kind of fish is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.60,0:24:25.48,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}ginger{\i0}, you dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.60,0:24:25.48,Signs,,0,0,0,,shôga
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.48,0:24:27.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You really are hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.48,0:24:27.23,Signs,,0,0,0,,shô ga nai
